&lt;h3&gt;About One Acre Fund&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Founded in 2006, One Acre Fund equips 5.5 million smallholder farmers to make their farms more productive. Across nine countries that together are home to two-thirds of Africa&#39;s farmers, we provide high-quality farm supplies, tree seedlings, accessible credit, modern agronomic training, and a wide range of other agricultural services. On average, this model enables any farmer to increase their income and assets on supported land by more than 35 percent, while permanently improving their resilience. This is all made possible by our team of 9,000+ full-time staff, drawn from diverse backgrounds and professions.&amp;nbsp;To learn more, please see our&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://oneacrefund.org/careers/why-work-here&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Why Work Here&lt;/a&gt; blog post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our Kenya program, founded in 2006, operates under the local brand Tupande. Close to 500 staff in our Kakamega headquarters support 1,747 field staff and serve more than 1 million farmers. In Nairobi, around 50 staff support global functions like procurement, recruitment, government relations, and communications.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;About the Role&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Seeking an Administration Supervisor with 3+ years&#39; manufacturing or industrial experience to manage office operations, casual labour contracting, and utility documentation for a biochar facility.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Office and Records Management&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage day-to-day office operations including supplies, equipment, and a clean and organized workspace&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate records of administrative activities including employee files, invoices, and operational documentation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Handle incoming and outgoing communications including phone calls, emails, and correspondence&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate meetings, appointments, and travel arrangements for facility leadership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Casual Labor Administration&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own casual labor contracting for the Biochar facility, ensuring sufficient casuals required for production at any given time&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate records of casual engagement periods, daily rates, and shift deployment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure processing of casual payroll in line with company policies and Kenyan labor regulations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure casual labor documentation complies with company policy and Kenyan labor law&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Compliance and Customer Service&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure all administrative activities comply with company policies and relevant regulatory requirements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Greet and assist visitors, clients, suppliers, and verification auditors, ensuring a professional experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain confidentiality of sensitive information at all times&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Monitoring, Reporting, and Verification&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collect and submit all utility documentation required for MRV, including electricity, diesel, water, and packaging&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain employment records (number of employees, roles, demographics)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support stakeholder engagement and grievance documentation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;May manage an Administration Officer later on&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;May manage 2-4 suppliers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
