&lt;h3&gt;About the Role&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Seeking a hands-on Extension and Aggregation Officer to run a cashew buying center and aggregate raw cashew nuts on Kenya&#39;s coast — building market access opportunities for smallholder farmers in a scaling program.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Manage the buying center:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Operate it during scheduled hours.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Keep it clean, organized, and secure.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Handle, dry, and store RCN according to Tupande standard operating procedures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Aggregate accurately and with integrity:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Weigh RCN accurately.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Quality control each purchase (sorting damaged, moldy, or poor-quality nuts).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Process payments via FieldPro and ensure compliance (i.e., KRA/eTIMS).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Escalate any disputes, discrepancies, or irregularities to your Supervisor immediately.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Support farmers in the field:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver agronomic training to farmers in your assigned location.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate purchase and quality requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Executive field visits and prepare field reports for your Supervisor.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate with Tupande Agents and Zone Supervisors to mobilize farmers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Collect accurate data:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interview farmers and brokers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Record data on time using provided digital tools (i.e., stock take, farmer/broker scouting).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Escalate any data-quality issues to your Supervisor.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Coordinate logistics:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with loaders, Tupande’s logistics team, and your Supervisor to schedule and execute RCN collection.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Career Growth and Development&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;We have a strong culture of constant learning and we invest in developing our people. You’ll have weekly check-ins with your manager, access to mentorship and training programs, and regular feedback on your performance. We hold career reviews every six months, and set aside time to discuss your aspirations and career goals. You’ll have the opportunity to shape a growing organization and build a rewarding long-term career.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
