&lt;h3&gt;About One Acre Fund&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Founded in 2006, One Acre Fund equips 5.5 million smallholder farmers to make their farms more productive. Across nine countries that together are home to two-thirds of Africa&#39;s farmers, we provide high-quality farm supplies, tree seedlings, accessible credit, modern agronomic training, and a wide range of other agricultural services. On average, this model enables any farmer to increase their income and assets on supported land by more than 35 percent, while permanently improving their resilience. This is all made possible by our team of 9,000+ full-time staff, drawn from diverse backgrounds and professions.&amp;nbsp;To learn more, please see our&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://oneacrefund.org/careers/why-work-here&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Why Work Here&lt;/a&gt; blog post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our Kenya program, founded in 2006, operates under the local brand Tupande. Close to 500 staff in our Kakamega headquarters support 1,747 field staff and serve more than 1 million farmers. In Nairobi, around 50 staff support global functions like procurement, recruitment, government relations, and communications.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;About the Role&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Seeking a Logistics and MRV (Monitoring, Reporting, and Verification) Coordinator with 2-3 years&#39; experience in distribution and/or carbon markets&amp;nbsp; and/or MRV to lead the distribution of biochar and manage the MRV program.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;dMRV Program Leadership&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design, implement, and manage the facility&#39;s dMRV system, covering feedstock inputs, production outputs, quality measurements, and carbon sequestration calculations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure data collection processes across all shifts are accurate, consistent, and traceable to applicable carbon standards (e.g., Puro.earth, EBC, IBI, or other relevant frameworks)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee and support the Lab/Quality Technicians in their data recording responsibilities to ensure dMRV-grade data quality&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare and submit periodic monitoring reports, verification reports, and audit-ready documentation for carbon credit issuance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Liaise with third-party verifiers, auditors, and certification bodies during verification cycles&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain data management systems, dashboards, and reporting templates for dMRV purposes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Train all relevant staff on dMRV data recording requirements and the importance of data integrity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay current on evolving carbon standards, methodology requirements, and dMRV best practices in the biochar sector&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute towards process improvement with Production and Logistics stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Distribution Logistics Coordination&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the end-to-end forecasting process that translates production output into logistics requirements for Soko Logistics, including expected truck volume, required capacity, and resource preparation needed ahead of each distribution cycle&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead a standing weekly planning sync with the Soko Logistics Manager to review the upcoming week&#39;s distribution forecast and confirm operational readiness before the week begins&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the dedicated point of contact between Biochar production and Soko Logistics, driving alignment on schedules, volumes, and delivery execution&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Plan and adjust delivery schedules in coordination with the Production Coordinator based on production output and farmer demand&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage delivery records and customer order tracking&lt;/li&gt;
